&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At McMaster-Carr, working in distribution isn’t just a job, it’s a career. As a Distribution Operations Specialist, you’ll have responsibilities across multiple areas of our world-class facility, performing essential work to ensure our customers receive the parts they need accurately and on time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a &lt;strong&gt;fully onsite&lt;/strong&gt; role at our brand-new facility located at 15333 Independence Parkway, Fort Worth, TX. It’s an exciting time at McMaster-Carr as we grow into our new regional headquarters in Fort Worth—a modern, automated distribution facility that will help support Texas customers with the excellent service and innovative solutions that define our company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;McMaster-Carr is a leading e-commerce company that industrial customers have trusted for over 120 years. Our products help them get manufacturing lines back up quickly, keep operations running smoothly, and prototype the next generation of innovative solutions. We earn and keep that trust by offering the right products, making them easy to find, and delivering them fast, so our customers can solve problems with greater speed, precision, and ease. Behind it all are our people: exceptional and resourceful problem-solvers who take pride in getting every detail right for our customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll begin by learning and mastering one core role within our facility. Once you’ve built proficiency in that role, you’ll expand your skillset through experiences such as:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handling oversized or heavy inventory using powered industrial vehicles (training provided)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparing outgoing packages and conducting quality checks to ensure presentation and accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fulfilling orders accurately to help customers meet their business needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on role in a fast-paced environment, ideal for individuals who enjoy physical work and are results-oriented self-starters. Our warehouse is clean, temperature-controlled, and equipped with technology to help you do your best work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;A bachelor&#39;s degree is preferred for this role.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for dependable, adaptable, and hard-working individuals excited to contribute to a highly organized and evolving distribution environment. You may come from a background in retail, military, education, or something entirely different. What matters most is that you have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and a commitment to accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Physical ability to work on your feet and perform repetitive tasks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with adhering to structured processes and making justified decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to train on material handling equipment (experience is a plus but not required)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A focus on safety of themselves and others&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A team mindset, strong work ethic, and a desire to grow through hands-on work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cash Compensation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Total cash compensation ranges from $95,500 - $108,500 annually, which includes annual cash profit sharing based on company profitability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer comprehensive benefits to support employees and their dependents, such as:&lt;/p&gt;
